            <thetext>Somewhat new kinds of jobs were introduced with &#39;watch&#39; or &#39;source-server&#39;, such that they can easily be put into the background. While this is done by OS/shell features (e.g. trailing ampersand, or Ctrl-Z), the user would nevertheless benefit from a way to stop those jobs offered by the generator (i.e. non-OS-specific).

Internally, this could be handled via temporary PID info, as Thomas suggested. Ideas would be to introduce explicit &quot;stop&quot; variants for those jobs, or a more generic CLI param that goes with the &quot;start&quot; jobs to cancel the corresponding background processes.</thetext>
